Welcome to the SparkFun developer employment application.

*******************************************
  OFFICIAL JOB DESCRIPTION: PHP DEVELOPER
*******************************************
 *
 * PHP Developer
 * 
 * SparkFun Electronics is hiring developers!  Check out our website,
 * www.sparkfun.com, to get an idea of who we are / what we do.  More
 * below...
 * 
 * About the company:
 *
 * - We're a small/medium company that's very young (only 7.7 years old) and
 *   growing very fast.
 * - Despite our growth we remain relaxed and fun.
 * - We throw lots of parties, have dogs on staff, and our break room has a
 *   tweeting keggerator.
 * - This place is like an invention shop.  Curious new toys are being built
 *   all the time.
 * - We like to host unique events like our annual Autonomous Vehicle
 *   Competition or this fall's Antimov: a competition for robots with
 *   extravagant self-destruct mechanisms.
 *
 * About the position:
 *
 * - You'll assist an established core of developers to build new features for
 *   the SparkFun website and our internal content management system, all of
 *   which is of custom design.
 * - You'll work closely with other SparkFun employees to build tools to make
 *   their lives easier.  Grateful employees have been known to show gratitude
 *   with candy.
 * - Skilled coders are encouraged to contribute ideas for architectural
 *   changes, not just mindlessly crank out code.  You'll be proud of what you
 *   get to build here.
 * - Work environment is definitely not soul-crushing, unlike many corporate
 *   shops that pay the big bucks.
 * - Benefits:
 *   + HSA/FSA health plan
 *   + 401k matching up to 4%
 *   + Eco pass
 *   + 2 weeks paid vacation to start, 3 weeks after 1 full year of employment
 *   + Yearly continuing education/professional development fund
 * 
 * Skills you have that will make me want to hire you:
 *
 * - Proficiency with PHP/MySQL (specifically within an MVC framework)
 * - Proficiency with HTML/CSS/JavaScript
 * - Experience building AJAX-powered web applications
 *
***

HOW TO APPLY:

1. Fork this repository.

2. Look at the README in all four directories and follow the instructions.

3. Send details on where to find your hosted repo to
   it_applications@sparkfun.com.

If you aren't comfortable applying in public, you're welcome to require
authentication, host as a private repository on GitHub, or otherwise obscure
your repo.
